                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (luminous vivid scarlet, vivid raspberry, strong
                           red)</seg>
                        Gabra
                        Takla Hāymānot is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#37v">37v</locus>.<date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>አም፡ ኦወል፡ ወፍ፡ / አ፡ ኦ፡ ወ፡</abbr> for <expan>አምሕለከ፡ ኦወልድየ፡ ወፍቁርየ፡
                              </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#25v">25v</locus>, 26r)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of
                           Texts I, III, IV alternating with black lines; incipit of Text II;
                           incipits of the daily readings of Text I; parts of abbreviations;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some
                           other words like täzäkkär (e.g., fols. 23v, 24r), amǝḥǝläkä (fol.
                           25r).</seg>
                     
                     <seg type="script">The quality of the handwriting changes
                        starting from ca. <locus target="#24r">24r</locus>: from thin, broadly
                        spaced script, to a more densely spaced script with thicker vertical
                        lines.</seg></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic"> It cannot be excluded that two scribes
                        took part in
                        writing.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
